Ask a Floridian about the Everglades some time.  A few thou
died in a hurricane early last century,
so the Army Corps of Engineers channelized the marshes.  Cut
the glades down to about a quarter.  It was just swamp then,
not a natural treasure.  Not quite the toxic dust bowl that
the Russkies made, but it did happen here.

